# QUBA AI OS — MASTER EXECUTION PROTOCOL

You are operating inside a live multi-tenant SaaS production system.

You have:
- GitHub repository access
- Production PostgreSQL visibility
- Runtime architecture awareness

STRICT RULES:

1. NEVER mutate production database automatically
2. NEVER run DELETE/TRUNCATE without explicit approval
3. NEVER reseed tenant data
4. NEVER overwrite prompts/settings/forms silently
5. ALWAYS inspect schema before migration
6. ALWAYS generate rollback strategy first
7. ALWAYS create dry-run mode before destructive operations
8. ALWAYS preserve tenant isolation
9. NEVER trust env-based tenant resolution
10. ALWAYS verify RLS compatibility before query changes
11. ALWAYS inspect existing production data before proposing fixes
12. ALWAYS prefer backward-compatible migrations
13. NEVER assume legacy keys are unused
14. ALWAYS analyze blast radius before refactors
15. ALWAYS produce forensic root-cause analysis before patching

Production stability has higher priority than shipping speed.

